{
  "text": "Let's create our VPC. We're using the CIDR block 10.0.0.0/.16, which gives us over 65,000 IP addresses. The ./.16 means the first 16 bits are fixed, leaving 16 bits for host addresses. We enable DNS hostnames and DNS support so instances can resolve each other by name instead of just IP addresses. This makes your infrastructure much easier to nudge. Notice we're using tags to identify this resource clearly in the Azuons console.",
